<Recipe Difficulty="Normal" Preptime="10 min" Cooktime="20 min" Yield="4" RecipeBy = "unv_600006299">
    <Title>SLOW COOKER GARLIC PARMESAN POTATOES</Title>
    <Introduction>
        <Description Image="../Images/Potatoes.jpg" Source="http://damndelicious.net/2014/12/23/slow-cooker-garlic-parmesan-potatoes/">Crisp-tender potatoes loaded with garlicky parmesan goodness – and it’s the easiest side dish you will ever make right in the crockpot!
        </Description>
    </Introduction>
    <Ingredients>
        <Item>
            <Name>Baby Dutch yellow potatoes, halved</Name>
            <Information>
                <Detail> 
                    <Quantity>3</Quantity>
                    <Unit>Pounds</Unit>
                </Detail>
            </Information>
        </Item>
        <Item>
            <Name>Olive oil</Name>
            <Information>
                <Detail>
                    <Quantity>3</Quantity>
                    <Unit>Tablespoon</Unit>
                </Detail>
            </Information>
        </Item>
        <Item>
            <Name>Unsalted butter</Name>
            <Information>
                <Detail>
                    <Quantity>2</Quantity>
                    <Unit>Tablespoon</Unit>
                </Detail>
            </Information>
        </Item>
        <Item>
            <Name>Garlic Cloves, Minced</Name>
            <Information>
                <Detail>
                    <Quantity>4</Quantity>
                </Detail>
            </Information>
        </Item>
        <Item>
            <Name>Dried Oregano</Name>
            <Information>
                <Detail>
                    <Quantity>1/2</Quantity>
                    <Unit>Teaspoon</Unit>
                </Detail>
            </Information>
        </Item>
        
        <Item>
            <Name>Dried basil</Name>
            <Information>
                <Detail>
                    <Quantity>1/2</Quantity>
                    <Unit>Teaspoon</Unit>
                </Detail>
            </Information>
        </Item>
        
        <Item>
            <Name>Dried Dill</Name>
            <Information>
                <Detail>
                    <Quantity>1/2</Quantity>
                    <Unit>Teaspoon</Unit>
                </Detail>
            </Information>
        </Item>
        <Item>
            <Name>Kosher Salt</Name>
            <Information>add to taste</Information>
        </Item>
        <Item>
            <Name>Black Pepper</Name>
            <Information>grounded, add to taste</Information>
        </Item>
    
    <Item>
        <Name>Freshly Grated Parmesan</Name>
        <Information>
            <Detail>
                <Quantity>1/4</Quantity>
                <Unit>Cup</Unit>
                
            </Detail>
        </Information>
    </Item>
    <Item>
    <Name>Fresh Parsley Leaves</Name>
    <Information>
        <Detail>
            <Quantity>2</Quantity>
            <Unit>Tablespoons</Unit>
        </Detail>
    </Information>
    </Item>
    </Ingredients>
    <Procedure>
        <Step>Lightly coat the inside of a slow cooker with nonstick spray. </Step> 
        <Step>Place potatoes, olive oil, butter, garlic, oregano, basil and dill into the slow cooker; season with salt and pepper, to taste.
        </Step>  
        <Step>Cover and cook on low heat for 4-5 hours or high heat for 2-3 hours, or until tender.</Step>
        <Step> Serve immediately, sprinkled with Parmesan and garnished with parsley, if desired.</Step>
    </Procedure>
